1
00:00:05,120 --> 00:00:07,490
August 13,1975

2
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:33,280
Tell mama I'm going to play.

3
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:37,120
You better be home before the streetlights come on, girl.

4
00:00:41,660 --> 00:00:44,970
fireflies turn into fairies at the end of summer.

5
00:00:45,090 --> 00:00:46,840
Why fairies?

6
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:49,240
'Cause, they do.

7
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:50,880
You made that up.

8
00:00:50,930 --> 00:00:53,370
You never see fireflies in the winter, right?

9
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:55,820
In brooklyn, we never saw them ever.

10
00:00:55,870 --> 00:00:57,780
'Cause they turn into fairies, that's why.

11
00:00:57,830 --> 00:01:00,430
Yeah?And go where?

12
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:04,360
Their castle in the sky, where nothing ever dies.

13
00:01:04,410 --> 00:01:05,950
But not all fairies make it.

14
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:06,850
Why not?

15
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,060
'Cause the trolls catch them.

16
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:12,550
Where do the fireflies really go, melanie?

17
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:14,230
I don't know.

18
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:22,710
My brother said when summer ends,
you won't play with me anymore.

19
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:23,430
Why?

20
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:26,550
'Cause you're white, and I'm black.

21
00:01:26,590 --> 00:01:28,940
But we're best friends.

22
00:01:29,230 --> 00:01:31,890
- Forever?
- Forever and a day.

23
00:01:32,130 --> 00:01:35,480
Maybe when summer ends, the fireflies go to heaven.

24
00:01:35,530 --> 00:01:38,980
Yeah, maybe.

25
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:23,330
Let's get forensics in here,
see if they can pick anything up.

26
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:26,120
- Lil.
- Morning, boss.

27
00:02:26,170 --> 00:02:27,080
What do you got?

28
00:02:27,130 --> 00:02:30,200
Ever hear of a letter arriving 31 years too late?

29
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,400
Too late for what?

30
00:02:31,450 --> 00:02:33,610
Save the life of a young girl.

31
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:35,030
Former postman lived here?

32
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:36,380
Died last week.

33
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:40,020
Refused to deliver mail to blacks on his route back in '75.

34
00:02:40,050 --> 00:02:41,720
Welcome to the U.S.Postal service.

35
00:02:41,780 --> 00:02:44,550
His family found bags of mail stashed in the basement.

36
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,860
The inspector's been sifting for hours.

37
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:48,630
This was in one of them.

38
00:02:49,790 --> 00:02:52,140
From an eight-year-old girl, melanie campbell.

39
00:02:52,190 --> 00:02:53,820
Went missing in '75.

40
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:55,980
Body never found.Presumed homicide.

41
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:58,190
Postcard's addressed to her best friend,
next door neighbor,

42
00:02:58,230 --> 00:03:01,790
cherise pierce, black girl.
Take a look.

43
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,990
"The trolls got me.

44
00:03:04,140 --> 00:03:05,340
" Some kind of message?

45
00:03:05,390 --> 00:03:08,880
It was postmarked the day melanie disappeared.

46
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:10,710
Cry for help.

47
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:13,580
31 years too late to save her.

48
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:16,460
Maybe not too late to catch her killer.

