52
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:49,420
Melanie campbell, age eight.

53
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:54,350
Abducted from her bedroom,
night of october 23, 1975.

54
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,650
Her bloody ballet shshoe found in a nearby park.

55
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:57,620
Tender-age search.

56
00:03:57,670 --> 00:03:59,630
Lot of time, manpower on this one.

57
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,750
Body never recovered.

58
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:03,480
Theory was an intruder came in
through a broken basement window.

59
00:04:03,530 --> 00:04:07,360
A postcard was sent to her neighbor, cherise pierce.

60
00:04:07,410 --> 00:04:08,130
Never made it.

61
00:04:08,180 --> 00:04:09,380
These kids were tight.

62
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:11,210
Best friends, hung out 24/7.

63
00:04:11,260 --> 00:04:12,840
Not the only pierce in here.

64
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:17,380
Prime suspect at the time was cherise's
teenage brother, terrell pierce.

65
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:19,110
Based on what?

66
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:22,900
Kid had no record, straight-a student, Mr.Clean.

67
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:25,790
Neighbor id'd terrell in the campbells' backyard,
night of the abduction.

68
00:04:25,850 --> 00:04:28,940
In these words: "Saw that colored boy
monkeying around on

69
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:30,870
the side of their house.

70
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,080
" That's credible.

71
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,920
Lifted a partial palm print from
the campbells' basement window.

72
00:04:34,970 --> 00:04:36,070
No match to terrell.

73
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,320
Didn't stop them from interrogating him.

74
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:39,480
Six times.

75
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:42,830
Parents were questioned, too,
but dismissed as suspects.

76
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:45,330
'Cause once the black kid was id'd,
it was all about him.

77
00:04:45,380 --> 00:04:47,730
Brewerytown was lily-white back then.

78
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:49,610
Pierces were the first black family to move in.

79
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:51,190
That some kind of excuse?

80
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,490
Not an excuse, the times.

81
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:53,790
Aka white flight.

82
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,470
Families hightailing it to the burbs,

83
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:57,990
terrified that their property values would tank.

84
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,030
One way to spin it.

85
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:03,670
At least one white family stayed: The campbells.

86
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:06,120
Families of missing kids do that, refuse to move.

87
00:05:06,170 --> 00:05:09,470
Yeah, waiting for their child to walk through the door.

88
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:12,160
Lily's gonna talk to the parents.

89
00:05:12,220 --> 00:05:14,180
You want to take cherise and terrell?

90
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:15,530
Sure.

91
00:05:23,290 --> 00:05:26,170
Could be terrell didn't deserve any of this.

92
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:29,520
Neither did melanie.

93
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:43,080
"The trolls got me.

94
00:05:44,460 --> 00:05:48,720
" It was addressed to the girl next door,
cherise pierce.

95
00:05:48,970 --> 00:05:50,640
You think melanie wrote that?

96
00:05:50,690 --> 00:05:54,580
Possibly.Could "the trolls"
have meant something?

97
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:58,820
Melanie was always going on
about fairies and trolls and fireflies.

98
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:00,460
Quite an imagination.

99
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:02,090
But it was just child's talk.

100
00:06:02,140 --> 00:06:03,700
Melanie did not write this.

101
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:04,620
How do you know?

102
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:08,890
She just started the third grade,
and she didn't know cursive.

103
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:11,320
Of course melanie wrote that.
These are her words.

104
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:13,380
But anyone who heard her
playing would've known them.

105
00:06:13,430 --> 00:06:14,680
Who wrote it, then?

106
00:06:14,730 --> 00:06:16,410
Maybe the person who took her.

107
00:06:16,460 --> 00:06:19,520
What kind of a monster would do a thing like that?

108
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:22,270
That's what I'm here to find out, mrs.Campbell.

109
00:06:22,330 --> 00:06:24,590
- So you'll find melanie, too?
- Oh, frances.

110
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,420
She is alive.

111
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:30,060
It's been 31 years.

112
00:06:30,110 --> 00:06:33,360
I don't care if it's 131 years.

113
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:35,910
Melanie is out there.

114
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:40,740
Can I walk you out?

115
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,960
We are prisoners in this house
because my wife believes

116
00:06:55,010 --> 00:06:57,480
our daughter's gonna walk through that front door.

117
00:06:57,530 --> 00:06:59,640
Just thought you should know we're reopening the case.

118
00:06:59,690 --> 00:07:03,470
All I want is to bury my child.

119
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,680
I understand.

120
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:09,820
Then bring her home.

121
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:24,960
It was a lifetime ago.

122
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:27,760
I barely remember that girl.

123
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:32,130
You were best friends back when
blacks and whites didn't exactly mix.

124
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:33,820
Take a look around.

125
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:35,110
Still don't.

126
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,800
I know you probably got an unfair shake in '75.

127
00:07:37,850 --> 00:07:39,460
Probably?

128
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:42,000
Cops had me in the box for 16 hours at a time.

129
00:07:42,050 --> 00:07:43,150
That's rough.

130
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,980
Should've seen the '50s and '60s,
you want to talk rough.

131
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:50,580
You were id'd in the girl's yard
the night she disappeared.

132
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:54,700
By an old busybody who thought blacks
should go back to africa.

133
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,640
So that was a flat-out lie?

134
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,370
Flat-out.

135
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,180
Talk about you and melanie.

136
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:02,900
Like I said, it was long time ago.

137
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:06,820
"The trolls" mean anyone in particular?

138
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:11,800
Could be the difference between
finding melanie's killer or not.

139
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,490
Trolls were people we didn't like.

140
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:15,210
Go on.

141
00:08:15,260 --> 00:08:16,800
We had codes for everything.

142
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:20,820
I'd say something like: "Alvina lights a spark.

143
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:22,260
" Alvina lights a spark?

144
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:24,660
Code for: "I left a note on our clothesline.

145
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:26,720
" So who were the trolls?

146
00:08:26,770 --> 00:08:28,260
Almost everyone.

147
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:30,230
Our friendship wasn't looked on too kindly.

148
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,100
By who?

149
00:08:31,190 --> 00:08:35,120
The whole neighborhood had it out for us,
from the start.

150
00:08:35,170 --> 00:08:37,390
Everyone except melanie.

151
00:08:37,490 --> 00:08:56,280
Leave...!

152
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:57,760
get out of here, critters!

153
00:08:57,860 --> 00:09:06,340
Leave...!

154
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,410
What does "critters" mean, terrell?

155
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:12,990
Dad told you to go inside, cherise.

156
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:16,970
"Critters" means bugs and stuff.

157
00:09:18,170 --> 00:09:20,180
Oh.

158
00:09:20,230 --> 00:09:22,100
Want to see my fireflies?

159
00:09:22,190 --> 00:09:24,480
Are those...bugs?

160
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:26,260
Their booties light up at night.

161
00:09:27,190 --> 00:09:30,050
they do.Like magic.

162
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:32,880
I mean, if you believe in that stuff.

163
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:36,140
Quit talking to that girl!

164
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,250
Go home, melanie!

165
00:09:37,290 --> 00:09:38,980
You're not the boss of me, Mr.Wilson!

166
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:42,290
I told you to go home.
Now!

167
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:53,460
Leave...!

168
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:57,000
My mom said you can come over after dinner.

169
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:58,590
I live right here.

170
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:01,160
We can catch fireflies when it gets dark.

171
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,070
Okay.

172
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:03,300
See you later, alligator.

173
00:10:03,350 --> 00:10:05,700
After awhile, crocodile.

174
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:10,440
Quite a welcoming committee.

175
00:10:10,490 --> 00:10:14,420
Courtesy of hank wilson, head of the civic club.

176
00:10:14,470 --> 00:10:17,680
Civic club?
More like a lynch mob.

177
00:10:17,730 --> 00:10:20,650
Racists parading around as
neighborhood associations.

178
00:10:20,710 --> 00:10:22,620
Who was this bozo?

179
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:24,520
He owned the local hardware store.

180
00:10:24,570 --> 00:10:28,450
To him, the only thing worse than us
were whites who didn't go along.

181
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:30,660
Like melanie.

182
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:36,270
Our friendship might have cost her her life.

183
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:53,220
It was our neighborhood, not theirs.

184
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:56,340
Your family was there for 30 years,
then, here come the coloreds.

185
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:58,260
And to make matters worse, little melanie

186
00:10:58,310 --> 00:11:00,180
campbell gets all buddy-buddy with the black girl.

187
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,340
Could make a die-hard racist like you blow a gasket.

188
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:04,260
Whoa, hold on there.

189
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:08,520
When melanie disappeared, all the
white people got spooked, moved out.

190
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:10,440
Had to sell my house at a loss.

191
00:11:10,490 --> 00:11:11,640
Boo-hoo.

192
00:11:11,700 --> 00:11:12,870
We were working people.

193
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,220
House was all we had.

194
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:16,620
Beat up your own kid regular for looking at you funny.

195
00:11:16,670 --> 00:11:18,010
What's that got to do with anything?

196
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:19,690
Maybe you let the fists fly with melanie.

197
00:11:19,740 --> 00:11:21,560
Lippy little kid must have pissed you off.

198
00:11:21,610 --> 00:11:24,300
I was working at the hardware store
the night she disappeared.

199
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,070
We'll check that.

200
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:29,290
Go ahead, and while you're at it,
check out a guy by the name of wes floyd.

201
00:11:29,340 --> 00:11:30,150
Who's he?

202
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:34,130
Real estate scumbag that was creeping
around the neighborhood back then.

203
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:36,810
Tried to scare all the white folks into moving.

204
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:38,890
Why?So he could clean up?

205
00:11:38,940 --> 00:11:42,250
Type like that would do anything for a buck.

206
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,340
You hear about that break-in the other day?

207
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:46,210
Right down the street.

208
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:47,800
Thank goodness no one was hurt.

209
00:11:47,850 --> 00:11:50,560
Imagine what would happen if that family was home?

210
00:11:50,561 --> 00:11:51,571
That's terrified!

211
00:11:51,590 --> 00:11:55,330
Known fact-- blacks move in, crime goes up.

212
00:11:55,370 --> 00:11:58,580
Six, seven, eight, nine, ten...

213
00:11:58,630 --> 00:12:01,600
" bad things happen to decent people.

214
00:12:01,650 --> 00:12:03,140
Well, we all know one another here.

215
00:12:03,190 --> 00:12:07,140
Oh, for now, sure, but once the dam breaks,
no stopping who comes in.

216
00:12:07,190 --> 00:12:09,350
You don't want to be the last to leave, do you?

217
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,310
I guess not, but...

218
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:14,870
place like genessee creek offers a safe
environment for families like yours.

219
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:19,040
State-of-the-art kitchens.Big yard.A pool.

220
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:20,890
This heat, a pool would be nice.

221
00:12:20,940 --> 00:12:21,800
Huh?

222
00:12:21,850 --> 00:12:24,830
Don't you fall for it, frances!

223
00:12:25,350 --> 00:12:26,900
Get out of here.

224
00:12:26,920 --> 00:12:28,940
I know what you're doing.

225
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:31,140
Just doing business.

226
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:33,300
Showing the nice lady the homes I have for sale.

227
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:36,270
You're trying to scare whites
out of this neighborhood,

228
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:38,120
but nobody here's leaving.

229
00:12:38,170 --> 00:12:40,420
Except the spooks over there.

230
00:12:40,470 --> 00:12:42,730
It's our neighborhood.

231
00:12:43,690 --> 00:12:45,890
Sure it is.

232
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:50,630
My husband would never agree.

233
00:12:58,090 --> 00:13:00,670
Neighborhood's gonna tip one day soon,

234
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,880
and you'll be the last white face around.

235
00:13:02,930 --> 00:13:05,470
Not if I can help it.

236
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:10,310
And if one bad thing happens to some nice little white kid?

237
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:14,190
Won't be up to you.

238
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:22,990
His houses in the suburbs
weren't selling worth squat.

239
00:13:23,090 --> 00:13:26,730
Then melanie disappears and he makes a killing.

240
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:29,510
Neighborhood tipped in, like, eight seconds.

241
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:31,170
Thanks for sharing.

242
00:13:31,220 --> 00:13:34,380
Now get before i drop-kick you out of here.

243
00:13:39,170 --> 00:13:40,940
Genessee creek.

244
00:13:40,990 --> 00:13:44,130
It's that tony subdivision over near abington.

245
00:13:44,230 --> 00:13:46,770
Lot of people made a killing off of white flight.

246
00:13:46,820 --> 00:13:50,460
Sounds like this wes floyd guy was one of them.

247
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:02,950
I see your real estate ads all over the place, wes.

248
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,570
Bus stops, billboards.

249
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:06,510
I do well.

250
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,300
And to think, it all started with genessee creek

251
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:12,370
and the abduction and murder of a little girl.

252
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,200
I'm a businessman, not a killer.

253
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:18,930
You made out like a bandit after
melanie campbell disappeared.

254
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:21,000
Sold 12 homes in one week.

255
00:14:21,050 --> 00:14:23,300
They say you make your own luck.

256
00:14:23,350 --> 00:14:25,940
Maybe you made yours.

257
00:14:26,050 --> 00:14:30,070
The timing was fortuitous, so arrest me.

258
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:31,600
Already have a record, wes.

259
00:14:31,660 --> 00:14:35,580
Silly trespassing charges for putting
a few "sold" signs in people's yards.

