00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,950
Terrell said that, too.

527
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,680
But I don't want to stick with my own.

528
00:29:24,730 --> 00:29:26,500
I want to be with you, cherise.

529
00:29:26,550 --> 00:29:27,990
Me, too, mel.

530
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:29,600
You're my best friend.

531
00:29:29,650 --> 00:29:33,400
- Forever?
- And a day.

532
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:43,400
Can't keep away from that critter, can you?

533
00:29:43,450 --> 00:29:44,790
What do you want, dale?

534
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:48,390
I drive to this critter's house to
scare her, and what do I see?

535
00:29:48,770 --> 00:29:50,980
This one trying to sneak off.

536
00:29:51,070 --> 00:29:53,230
Thought you could get away, huh?

537
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:58,160
I got beat because my dad thinks
I spray-painted your house.

538
00:29:58,210 --> 00:30:00,330
- Did you?
- No.

539
00:30:00,380 --> 00:30:03,930
And now the whole neighborhood's gonna
move out and he says it's 'cause of me.

540
00:30:07,550 --> 00:30:09,270
He hates me.

541
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:11,910
You're scaring us.

542
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:14,160
None of this would've happened if you hadn't moved here.

543
00:30:14,210 --> 00:30:16,700
I wanna go home.

544
00:30:17,330 --> 00:30:19,510
Melanie, run!

545
00:30:26,980 --> 00:30:31,380
I heard the gunshots, and I knew,
and I did nothing.

546
00:30:31,430 --> 00:30:33,450
Just kept running.

547
00:30:33,500 --> 00:30:35,610
Anyone would have.

548
00:30:35,660 --> 00:30:38,770
It's my fault we were in the woods.

549
00:30:41,230 --> 00:30:44,240
it's my fault she died.

550
00:30:44,390 --> 00:30:46,640
You weren't the one with the gun.

551
00:30:46,690 --> 00:30:53,060
Every night I would dream about him
coming into my room and taking me.

552
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:56,900
And then the dreams finally stopped.

553
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:00,140
Until now.

554
00:31:00,190 --> 00:31:02,730
The postcard.

555
00:31:03,450 --> 00:31:05,940
Just the other night I had a dream.

556
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:09,530
Melanie was with the fireflies.

557
00:31:09,970 --> 00:31:12,260
In a better place.

558
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,140
Heaven.

559
00:31:25,660 --> 00:31:28,630
We got an eyewitness who saw you shoot melanie.

560
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:29,860
That's crazy.

561
00:31:29,950 --> 00:31:31,230
Is it?

562
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:34,260
Cherise didn't see me shoot nobody.

563
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:41,430
Never said it was cherise, dale.

564
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,280
You sent the postcard.

565
00:31:43,380 --> 00:31:45,160
Insurance, to keep cherise quiet.

566
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,630
Your old man beat the crap outta you.

567
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,780
You were lookin' to get even.

568
00:31:47,830 --> 00:31:52,240
You followed cherise into the woods
that night, with your father's gun.

569
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:57,170
I never meant to hurt...

570
00:31:57,220 --> 00:31:58,800
oh, cut the bull!

571
00:31:58,850 --> 00:32:00,080
You shot at cherise!

572
00:32:00,130 --> 00:32:02,090
To scare her.

573
00:32:06,590 --> 00:32:10,770
But then...she screamed...

574
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:15,510
"and I thought...I thought I killed her.

575
00:32:15,660 --> 00:32:16,520
And I panicked.

576
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:18,730
So, you had to kill melanie, too--
she was a witness.

577
00:32:18,830 --> 00:32:20,990
Point of no return.

578
00:32:21,130 --> 00:32:26,150
My dad beat me every night for that critter lover thing.

579
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:32,790
If he found out about this...
he'd kill me.

580
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:36,670
So I did what I had to do.

581
00:32:36,770 --> 00:32:39,210
What, dale?

582
00:32:40,170 --> 00:32:45,970
I put her in the car and drove...For hours.

583
00:32:46,020 --> 00:32:48,990
Till we got to the west virginia state line.

584
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,330
Then what happened?

585
00:32:50,380 --> 00:32:53,210
Then I pulled off the road.

586
00:32:54,370 --> 00:32:58,630
It was dark and there was no one around.

587
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:03,320
Just us.

588
00:33:15,910 --> 00:33:17,840
stop.

589
00:33:18,370 --> 00:33:20,140
Right here.

590
00:33:21,630 --> 00:33:24,930
Why'd you have to be friends with that critter?

591
00:33:30,750 --> 00:33:32,190
why?

592
00:33:32,620 --> 00:33:35,450
I just want to go home.

593
00:33:38,060 --> 00:33:40,030
This is all your fault, you hear me.

594
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:42,520
'Cause you had to be friends with her.

595
00:33:42,910 --> 00:33:44,870
Please.

596
00:33:45,970 --> 00:33:48,130
Close your eyes.

597
00:33:52,820 --> 00:33:56,030
I want my mommy.

598
00:33:57,270 --> 00:33:59,620
You can't tell on me.

599
00:33:59,810 --> 00:34:01,780
Please.

600
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:04,000
Not anymore.

601
00:34:09,830 --> 00:34:16,190
And then I just...drove away.

602
00:34:29,930 --> 00:34:35,910
No unidentified child murder victims
that age in west virginia, 1975.

603
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,880
Doesn't make sense.

604
00:34:37,930 --> 00:34:39,080
Rural area.

605
00:34:39,130 --> 00:34:40,660
Animals could've carried her off.

606
00:34:40,710 --> 00:34:42,010
Or the body was never found.

607
00:34:42,060 --> 00:34:44,120
Interstate files are a joke.

608
00:34:44,170 --> 00:34:46,900
No national database on missing kids back then.

609
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:50,310
Kid crossed state lines, easy to fall through the cracks.

610
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:55,960
So even if the body was found, no way
to connect it to our missing philly girl.

611
00:34:56,120 --> 00:34:57,270
Needle in a haystack.

612
00:34:57,370 --> 00:34:59,860
Police report, west virginia, october '75.

613
00:34:59,910 --> 00:35:02,500
State trooper found a girl just off route 1.

614
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:05,570
She was shot but alive.Head injury.

615
00:35:05,620 --> 00:35:08,130
No memory of who she was or where she came from.

616
00:35:08,180 --> 00:35:11,530
Transported to the county hospital in critical condition.

617
00:35:11,580 --> 00:35:13,500
Then put in foster care.

618
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:15,950
Melanie's still alive?

619
00:35:21,020 --> 00:35:22,890
Excuse me?

620
00:35:24,620 --> 00:35:26,390
Are you jennifer robinson?

621
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:27,500
Yeah.

622
00:35:27,550 --> 00:35:30,110
Philadelphia pd.

623
00:35:30,140 --> 00:35:31,390
Okay.

624
00:35:31,440 --> 00:35:34,790
You were a gunshot victim in '75.

625
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:37,100
Ain't you folks a little late to the party?

626
00:35:37,190 --> 00:35:38,680
Hmy you don't remember the shooting?

627
00:35:38,730 --> 00:35:41,130
Or where you're from?

628
00:35:41,180 --> 00:35:43,330
Couldn't have been good, right?

629
00:35:43,380 --> 00:35:46,310
Family was probably the reason
I was in those woods.

630
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:48,210
You're wrong.

631
00:35:48,260 --> 00:35:50,840
Your mom and dad never stopped looking for you.

632
00:35:50,890 --> 00:35:55,300
Never stopped hoping you'd
walk through their door again.

633
00:35:55,790 --> 00:35:56,700
Is that right.

634
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:59,540
Their names are norman and frances campbell.

635
00:35:59,590 --> 00:36:01,650
Good people.

636
00:36:02,470 --> 00:36:05,150
I don't remember.Sorry.

637
00:36:07,220 --> 00:36:09,660
They never forgot you, melanie.

638
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:14,760
Is that my name?

639
00:36:14,810 --> 00:36:16,920
And your best friend was a girl named cherise.

640
00:36:16,970 --> 00:36:19,890
She was with you that night, in the woods.

641
00:36:22,430 --> 00:36:26,790
A lot of people still waitin'...
for you to come home.

642
00:36:27,940 --> 00:36:30,050
I should get back to work.

643
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:33,450
You and cherise left notes for each other on the...

644
00:36:33,500 --> 00:36:35,790
on the clothesline.

645
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:39,540
You believed in fireflies and fairies.

646
00:36:39,550 --> 00:36:41,760
Please.Stop.

647
00:36:41,810 --> 00:36:44,040
That's why he brought you into the woods.

648
00:36:44,090 --> 00:36:46,390
Because you were brave.

649
00:36:46,970 --> 00:36:49,170
In a world that wasn'T.

650
00:36:53,670 --> 00:37:02,470
I remember...I wasn't alone.In the woods.

651
00:37:02,910 --> 00:37:05,830
Because the fireflies were there...

652
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:09,660
telling me heaven had to wait.

653
00:37:10,090 --> 00:37:13,060
'Cause I had to live.

